                    <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/444</idno>
                    <idno type="URI">http://viaf.org/viaf/sourceID/SRP|person_444</idno>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-444">
                        The author of a commentary on the Psalms and other works. Possibly a disciple of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/552">Ishoʿ bar Nun</persName>.
                    </note>
                    <note type="disambiguation" source="#bib444-3 #bib444-4 #bib444-5 #bib444-6 #bib444-7">
                        Assemani puts this Denha in the 8th century, but he must have rather been active in the 9th century if he is the person meant by 
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/823">John bar Zoʿbi</persName>, who (in a 
                        British Library manuscript catalogued by Wright) identified the Denha 
                        who authored a commentary on <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/342">Aristotle</persName>'s <title>Analytics</title> as a disciple of the 
                        Church of the East catholicos 
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/552">Ishoʿ bar Nun</persName>. Barsoum's identification of this Denha with an apparently West Syriac <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/160">Denha</persName> who wrote a 
                        certain treatise against heretics is to be questioned.
                    </note>
                    <floruit notBefore="0750" notAfter="0950" syriaca-computed-end="0950-01-01" syriaca-computed-start="0750-01-01" source="#bib444-1">9th cent.?</floruit>
